column5: Our group is heading for Lac Seul next week. This will be the first time we have fished this lake. We will be fishing the lower central part of the lake at Black Bay Outpost. Can anybody tell me what we can expect and where and how to catch some Walleye...Thanks
http://www.justfishontario.com/reports.htm has two fishing reports from Lac Seul, both good reports, they will tell you what's happening. Looks like a good bite in the bays where the water is warmer.
Just came back from Lac Seul Lodge, Check my other posts & check with Dan, the owner, He'll point you in the right direction for great fishing. Good luck!
